{"actual_usd":0.12422,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":183,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24295,"reply":"\"I wouldn't put it either of those ways.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is to ruin a vessel by forcing the shape too quickly.* \"Not three gods... and not one God wearing three masks. One God, truly—Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, each really Himself, and not just a costume change.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"That water picture sounds tidy, but it bends the truth. Ice, liquid, steam—that's one thing changing forms. But the Son prays to the Father. The Father sends the Spirit. They aren't just taking turns.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"Three Persons, one God. I know that's not neat like a little lesson-card. But some things are bigger than our tidy comparisons.\"\n\n\"What brought that to mind?\"","rolling_24h_usd":27.400480000000016,"run_id":"fe708ce9-f21d-44ec-999f-690cefd2a038"}
